c) The authority to permit the use of armed forces

ARTICLE 66 - The authority to declare a state of war in cases deemed legi-
timate by international law, and exclusive of cases rendered necessary by international
treaties to which Turkey is a party, or by rules of international comity, to send
TurkiSh enpe‘ditionary forces to foreign lands and to allow foreign armed forces to
bé'étht‘icshéa' in Turkey, is vested in the Turkish Grand National Assembly.

Forthegranting of such permission the National Assembly and the Senate shall
pass, resolutions in .joint session.
