Excerpt from the decision number 106 of the Supreme Board of Election
concerning the results of the constitulional referendum

«It was established that on July 9. 1961, the day of the referendum, the total
number of eligible voters in Turkey was 12.735.009, and a total number of 10.322.169
voters cast their ballots. Of these 10.282.561 ballots were valid and 39.608 were
invalid. The number of those -voting for the Constitution totaled 6.348.191 and those
against it 3.934.370.»
